the modernisation of Bhutan. Every Bhutanese will agree with me on this point as change led by globalisation is taking place rapidly everywhere in Bhutan. Because of these changes, the economy grew and prospered with exponential speed along with all other aspects of the society within this last century.

It was the modernisation that has transformed Bhutan from shepherds and hunters of wild animals into a society civilised with highly developed sense of courtesy and cooperation. Wherever we go around the world now, we have the best of manners as we are trained to carve well-nurtured and well-educated minds and those values are consistently kept alive by every Bhutanese living in rural and urban habitat.

We have well-known examples for carpets, frankincense and natural cosmetics and now we have a good number of young well-established businesses of various products which are recognised with tremendous approval in various countries across the world.

Having evolved over centuries, we have impeccable customs, values and traditions which emulate us as a nation of honour and respect. These human qualities give us a human face in the world community. As a traditional culture, a Buddhist society, and as a developing nation, Bhutan has provided an excellent example to the world to emulate.
